label: ABC2_mP16_14_e_e_2e-004
title: Manganite ($\gamma$-MnO(OH), $E0_{6}$) Structure
comments:
(Buerger, 1936) originally determined the positions of the manganese and oxygen atoms using the $B2_{1}/d$ setting of space group \#14.  This structure was given the {\em Strukturbericht} designation $E0_{6}$ in (Gottfried, 1938).  Much later, (Kohler, 1997) found the positions of the hydrogen atoms, and presented the data in the standard $P2_{1}/c$ setting of space group \#14. 
 \href{current_web_home_dir/ABC2_mP16_14_e_e_2e-003}{KNO$_{2}$ (III)}, \href{current_web_home_dir/ABC2_mP16_14_e_e_2e-004}{manganite (MnOOH)}, and \href{current_web_home_dir/ABC2_mP16_14_e_e_2e-005}{$\beta$-LiErO$_{2}$} have the same AFLOW label, ABC2\_mP16\_14\_e\_e\_2e. The structures are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files.
